1. The method returns an integer value.
2. The returned integer value is the majority element in the input array `arr`.
3. The majority element appears more than `⌊n / 2⌋` times in the input array `arr`.
4. The majority element always exists in the input array `arr`.
5. The method solves the problem in linear time.
6. The method solves the problem in `O(1)` space.
